President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate Sandra E. Clark of Maryland as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary to Burkina Faso. Clark is a career member of the Senior Foreign Service and has held various roles at the State Department, including Director of the Office of West African Affairs in the Bureau of African Affairs. She has also served as Deputy Chief of Mission of the United States Embassy in Dakar, Senegal, and as Deputy Coordinator of Assistance to Europe and Eurasia. Clark has a B.A. from Swarthmore College and a J.D. from Columbia University School of Law. She is fluent in French and Russian.